Recursion -

1)A function which Calls/Repeats itself is called as Recursion.
2)It breaks down complex parts into smaller parts and process it for further execution.
3)It contains -
a)Initiialization
b)Conditional
c)Increment and Decrement.
4)When a function calls itself inside it is called as a function.
5)Used to solve complex questions by diving bigger problems into  smalller ones.
6)Recursion uses Recusrsion Stack.
7)It takes more memory.
8)It uses Top down and Bottom up Approach.
